articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Chip designer Nvidia (NVDA.O) forecast third-quarter revenue above Wall Street targets on Wednesday, boosted by soaring demand for its chips that power nearly all the world's major artificial intelligence apps.
articles.title: Nvidia forecasts third-quarter revenue above Wall Street expectations

articles.author: Stephen Nellis, Max Cherney
articles.description: Nvidia's (NVDA.O) CEO Jensen Huang said he expects the artificial intelligence boom will last well into next year and made what could be the largest single bet yet in the tech sector to back up his optimism.
articles.title: Nvidia bets $25 bln that AI boom is far from over

articles.author: Hari Kishan
articles.description: Global stock markets are heading for a correction in coming months, though overall they should post marginal gains between now and the end of 2023, according to a majority of analysts polled by Reuters.
articles.title: Global stock market correction likely before year-end: Reuters poll

articles.author: Valerie Insinna, David Shepardson
articles.description: Boeing (BA.N) has recently identified a new 737 MAX quality problem involving supplier Spirit AeroSystems (SPR.N) that has resulted in improperly drilled holes on the aft pressure bulkhead, the planemaker said on Wednesday.
articles.title: New Boeing 737 MAX supplier defect to delay aircraft deliveries

articles.author: Julie Zhu
articles.description: Asian shares rallied on Thursday after blockbuster results from tech darling Nvidia (NVDA.O) boosted Wall Street and a retreat in U.S. bond yields eased pressure on borrowing costs globally.
articles.title: Asia stocks track Wall Street rally as treasury yields retreat

articles.author: Paul Lienert, Ben Klayman
articles.description: Hybrid gasoline-electric vehicles may not be dying as fast as some predicted in the auto sector’s rush to develop all-electric models.
articles.title: Focus: Gas-electric hybrid vehicles get a boost in the US from Ford, others

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia's Qantas Airways Ltd (QAN.AX) on Thursday posted a record annual profit and reiterated its expectations of a complete recovery in its group international capacity to return to pre-COVID levels in the second half of fiscal 2024.
articles.title: Qantas focuses on international capacity recovery after record annual profit

articles.author: Valerie Insinna, Allison Lampert
articles.description: An Embraer (EMBR3.SA) Legacy 600 executive jet, believed to have carried Wagner mercenary chief Yevgeny Prigozhin to his death on Wednesday, showed no sign of problem until a precipitous drop in its final 30 seconds, according to flight-tracking data.
articles.title: Russian mercenary Yevgeny Prigozhin's plane appeared fine on radar until last 30 seconds

articles.author: Nathan Layne, Joseph Ax
articles.description: The first Republican 2024 presidential debate on Wednesday opened with a focus on the U.S. economy, as eight contenders jockeyed for position behind the absent front-runner, Donald Trump.
articles.title: In Trump's absence, Republican hopefuls vie for position at first presidential debate

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The moon rover of India's Chandrayaan-3 exited the spacecraft on Thursday to begin its exploration of the lunar surface, local television channels reported.
articles.title: Moon rover exits India's Chandrayaan-3 spacecraft to explore lunar surface -TV
